item.title: Al Seminario
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Perched on a hilltop between Lucca and the coast, Al Seminario offers stunning views and a private location, but is close enough to the highway to make a good base for exploring the rest of Tuscany. Open the windows as you drive up into the hills and follow an unpaved road to the gates of this rustic four-bedroom villa; youll know youre on vacation when you sink into the infinity-edge pool with a panoramic view.
Al Seminario may be in the middle of the countryside, but it doesnt lack for amenities, starting with the vine-covered pergola that stretches along the front of the house. Dine under the shade of the wisteria at the table and chairs there, or stretch out on a chaise longue by the pool and listen to its waterfall. Theres an outdoor barbecue, too, to make al fresco dining a snap. Inside, theres Sky cable TV, a ping pong table and, for the smallest travelers, a baby cot and high chair.

item.title: Grape Villa
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded: Stunning Urban Contemporary. For those seeking the best of Urban Living!! Bright, airy open floor plan with 3 full bedrooms and 2 baths. Corner residence with 2 decks facing NorthEast and SouthEast. Contemporary European style kitchen featuring Caesar style counter tops, Fisher & Paykel dual drawer dishwasher and refrigerator. Ge Profile oven, electric range and microwave. Tandem parking for 2 cars. Come see what makes Aria Residence 303 so desirable.

item.title: Mas d'Eyragues
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Prepare to be charmed by the French countryside at Mas dEyragues. Set on nearly 7 acres outside Avignon, the villa has endless spots for families to explore, from a pool and ptanque court to a half tennis court and garden. Traditional decor gives the house an element of country chic, and nine bedrooms divided between the main house and guest house mean theres plenty of room for children of all ages.
Theres plenty to entertain during your stay, from a heated pool, al-fresco shower and jetted tub and outdoor sound system and bar to a ptanque court, half tennis court, swingset, trampoline and ping-pong table. Explore the garden, take the bicycles for a ride, try a local specialty on the barbecue, or relax at the outdoor sitting and dining areas. For evenings and rainy days, satellite TV, Wi-Fi, foosball and pool tables, a fitness room and bar and wine cellar offer plenty of diversions. For comfort and convenience, the villa is air-conditioned and has a fireplace and laundry facilities.

item.title: Villa Machiavelli
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
The views justify the trip to Italy at Villa Machiavelli. Just 20 minutes outside Florence in the Chianti Classico region, the recently restored 16th-century villa combines splendid Renaissance architecture and interiors with 21st century luxuries, topped off with panoramic views of the countryside. The villa accommodates up to twenty guests, but larger groups can rent the separate vineyard villa for more space.
Youll feel like Italian nobility at the fully staffed villa, formerly the home of the Machiavelli and Mazzei families. Drive in or use the helipad and explore the vineyards, olive groves and forest on the estate. Work up a sweat in the gym and cool off in the outdoor pool. For entertainment, theres a piano, satellite TV and Wi-Fi access; for comfort, theres air conditioning and an elevator.

item.title: La Veduta di Vertine
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Set on a beautiful hilltop in the Chianti Classico region, the spacious five-bedroom villa includes both a main house and guest cottage, two kitchens and four acres of land, so theres room for the whole family or a group of friends. A location within walking distance of Gaiole in Chianti and driving distance of Florence means its easy to explore the region.
The villa provides both the privacy of a home and hotel-worthy amenities. There are four acres of olive groves and lawns to stroll, a bocce court, billiards room, several terraces and a heated infinity pool with plenty of lounge chairs. Gather eggs from the propertys chickens and produce from its fruit trees, prepare dinner on the outdoor grill or pizza oven, select a vintage from the wine cellar and dine at the table in the stone courtyard.

item.title: Villa Ada
item.dc:creator: demo
item.content:encoded:
With views of both Tuscany and Umbria, a getaway to villa Ada will give you some perspective. The secluded seven-bedroom villa offers plenty of privacy, too, with a rural setting and separate accommodations for two families or larger groups of friends. But its not isolated; its location just outside Perugia makes it easy to visit the regions cities and towns.
The property is comprised of a main house and separate annex that have their own kitchens, living areas and bedrooms, but share a pool. Theres a grill, an outdoor dining area shaded by a rose-covered pergola and plenty of outdoor furniture in which to relax. Guests can arrange to use a shared tennis court, and indulgences like massages and yoga classes are available at extra cost. Even though youll be staying in the country, stay connected via the propertys Wi-Fi access.

item.title: Les Cavaliers
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Les Cavaliers villa is located close to Cevennes National Park, near Uzes in Provence. The area is ideal for enjoying the wonders of nature and the savors of wine. For the outdoorsy types, options for rafting and body rafting, mountain climbing, cave exploration and hunting are also situated near Les Cavaliers. A true marriage of modern luxury and old world charm, your dream French villa awaits!
The marvelous grounds at Les Cavaliers include a tennis court with an elevated and lit lounge area for spectators, two swimming poolsone for adults and one for children, a volleyball course, and a fitness lodge with a climbing wall and a sauna. Ample alfresco dining and lounging areas are also featured on the covered terrace. Use of the mountain and Quad bikes is complimentaryexplore the great outdoors! Inside, you will find a home theatre, satellite TV, multiple fireplaces, laptop and Wi-Fi access. Baby equipment is available, and the villa also includes various social games, video games and a childrens playroom.

item.title: Villa Splendida
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Villa Splendida is situated in the exclusive Borgo Egnazia resort, home to our most luxurious Puglia villa rentals. With its spacious private gardens and pool, 3-bedroom Villa Splendida makes a supremely relaxing retreat. Guests enjoy access to a wide range of luxury amenities including two beach clubs on the Adriatic Sea.
One of four adjoining villas, Villa Splendidas private garden and pool are separated from its neighbors by garden walls. Spread over three floors, youll find plenty of space in which to enjoy your splendid surroundings. The layout is comparable to our other Borgo Egnazia villas, however Villa Splendida benefits from a larger pool and garden with gazebo as well as a courtyard on the lower level.

item.title: Castell de Manresa
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Enjoy Mallorcas famed sun and sea from your own private estate at Castell de Manresa. Nestled on the bay of Pollensa close to several beaches, the circa-1715 main house boasts spectacular views over the Mediterranean and was recently renovated in modern style. A full staff and eight suite-style bedrooms make the property feel like a private boutique hotel.
During your stay, a cook, waiter and housekeeper will be on hand, leaving you free to relax by the pool or one of several outdoor lounge areas overlooking the sea. Work on your game on the tennis court or your routine in the gym, indulge in a sauna session or steam bath, and enjoy local fare from the barbecue at the al-fresco dining area. Thanks to the recent restoration, the villa has a sound system, laundry facilities and Wi-Fi.

item.title: Villa Il Palmeto
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Villa Il Palmeto is a stunning luxury villa located in the coveted Castelsardo area of Sardinia. Situated in the Gulf of Asinara, Castelsardo is the main town of the Anglona. A place of natural beauty, traditions and wonderful works of art, this medieval town makes a charming place to spend a holiday between the sea and a rich history in an idyllic climate.
The magnificent infinity swimming pool is shaped like a piano. The deck comes equipped with ample loungers and the garden and trees surrounding you will help put your mind at ease. The adjacent outdoor hot tub makes a great place to soothe any sore musclesperfect for after the flight. A barbeque sets the tone for good food, wine and laughs. You can also keep on top of your regular workouts at the fitness facility offered at Villa Il Palmeto.

item.title: Villa Sullivan
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
Brimming with personality, Villa Sullivan huddles into the Parian hillside, overlooking acres of bountiful olive yards. The villas enviable position offers views across a landscape dotted with pretty whitewash houses and out to sea, where you will find the islands miniature neighbor, Antiparos. Just 1km from the villa lies popular Farangas beach. Venture just a little further for quaint fishing villages Ageria and Aliki.
Cozily tucked among higgledy dry-stone walls and native plants, sits a comfy outdoor couch paired with a well-placed coffee table. Here you will find a little pocket of peace with postcard views, perfect for a laid back breakfast.

item.title: Villa Pep Simo Sea
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded: Perched dramatically on the hillside overlooking the dazzling Mediterranean, Villa Pep Simo Sea exudes an air of grandeur and opulence. From the impressive curved terrace you can enjoy a birds-eye view of the picturesque houses below. In the embrace of its turquoise infinity pool you will feel part of the sparkling sea beyond. Recline on an enticing sun lounger and the Ibizan sun will help soothe away your everyday cares and concerns. At Villa Pep Simo Sea youll be transported to the height of luxury and relaxation.

item.title: Camporempoli
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
With its arched doorways, stone exterior and beautifully restored interiors, villa Camporempoli is a charming hideaway. Its secluded location in the hills outside Siena and panoramic views of the Chianti area offer peace and quiet. A pool, outdoor dining area and garden are your own piece of the Tuscan countryside to enjoy.
The house is laid out around a central patio, so the airy living areas open to the patio on one side and the garden on the other. Step onto the terrace at the front of the house to take in the views, or duck under a vine-covered pergola to enjoy a glass of wine at the marble dining table. Theres a barbecue and a pool with a large shallow end perfect for children, not to mention an overflow effect and view of the hills. See if you can spot the villas resident cat amid the lush landscaping.

item.title: 1205 Coast Blvd
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded: This is a very rare opportunity to reside in a luxurious custom three level home in the heart of the village near shopping, restaurants and La Jolla cove. No two homes are just alike and this one will show you why. With breathtaking ocean views and detailed craftsmanship, this home gives the privacy and feel of a single family home with only 7 units situated within its complex. This home will not last! OPEN HOUSE Fri 7/3 10am-1pm Owner has spent nearly $700, 000 in upgrades and renovations.

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: crob
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!
